{
  "esm": "0.1.0",
  "metadata": {
    "name": "coupled_forced_refresh",
    "description": "A coupled, discretized, non-PDE forced model for the JL-J3 end-to-end loader-refresh test (ess-14f.6). Two states over a 3-cell index i in [1, 3]: Box `c[i]` accumulates a loader-fed source scaled by a CONST factor (D(c[i]) = scale[i]*src[i]), and Sink `d[i]` integrates the coupled tracer across the cell (D(d[i]) = c[i]). `scale` and `src` are undeclared forcing names resolved at build time through const_arrays (CONST `scale`, materialized once) and param_arrays (DISCRETE `src`, the live buffer the refresh callback writes in place). The Julia sibling of the Rust segmented_refresh_solve COUPLED_FORCED_JSON fixture (ess-14f.11). Forcing is piecewise-constant across cadence segments, so the dynamics integrate to an exact closed form checkable to solver tolerance."
  },
  "models": {
    "M": {
      "variables": {
        "c": { "type": "state", "shape": ["i"], "default": 0.0 },
        "d": { "type": "state", "shape": ["i"], "default": 0.0 }
      },
      "equations": [
        {
          "lhs": {
            "op": "arrayop", "args": [], "output_idx": ["i"], "ranges": { "i": [1, 3] },
            "expr": { "op": "D", "args": [{ "op": "index", "args": ["c", "i"] }], "wrt": "t" }
          },
          "rhs": {
            "op": "arrayop", "args": [], "output_idx": ["i"], "ranges": { "i": [1, 3] },
            "expr": {
              "op": "*",
              "args": [
                { "op": "index", "args": ["scale", "i"] },
                { "op": "index", "args": ["src", "i"] }
              ]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "lhs": {
            "op": "arrayop", "args": [], "output_idx": ["i"], "ranges": { "i": [1, 3] },
            "expr": { "op": "D", "args": [{ "op": "index", "args": ["d", "i"] }], "wrt": "t" }
          },
          "rhs": {
            "op": "arrayop", "args": [], "output_idx": ["i"], "ranges": { "i": [1, 3] },
            "expr": { "op": "index", "args": ["c", "i"] }
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  }
}
